By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Governor of Edo State, Godwin Obaseki has emerged the flagbearer of the Peoples Democratic Party to fly the party’s flag in the September governorship election in the state. He scored 1,952 votes out of 2,024 votes cast. Recall  that Pastor Osagie Ize -Iyamu had earlier in the week emerged the flagbearer of  the All Progressives Congress primary in the state. Governor Godwin Obaseki and Pastor Ize-Iyamu are the two strong contenders in the Edo governorship election scheduled to hold in September. Details later BENIN (Sundiata Post) - Less than 48 hours after the APC in Edo State picked Mr. Godwin Obaseki as it's flagbearer in the forthcoming governorship election in the state, the opposition PDP on Monday elected Mr. Osagie Ize-Iyamu as it's governorship candidate for the election.‎ Ize-Iyamu, a former member of… June 20, 2016 In "News" GUSAU (ZAMFARA) - Former Governor of Zamfara, Alhaji Mamuda Shinkafi, has again emerged the winner of the state's Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship primary election for the 2015 general polls.. The party's governorship primary, which held on Tuesday, was characterised by petitions and complaints where some of the aspirants alleged… December 12, 2014 In "News" By Victor Adeoti   Osogbo    -    Sen. Isiaka Adeleke, the winner of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship primary in Osun, says a great battle lies ahead in the Sept. 22 election in the state. Adeleke, in a statement on Monday in Osogbo, said that his emergence as the PDP… July 23, 2018 In "News"